=head1 Perl5 support in pugs

This document describes the bi-directional perl5 compatibility support.

=head1 TODO

=head2 perl6 calling perl5

=over

=item export

perl5_apply needs to push itself to additional caller stack, so
Exporter will try to modify a tied namespace, which then export
them to actual caller p6 namespace.

=item reference args

make getopt::long work.

=back

=head2 perl5 calling perl6

=over

=item libpugs.so

to be natively embedded in perl5

=item export

get the "is export" functions and refer them to perl5 symbol table.


=back

=cut
